# Claude Code instructions for {{ identity.project_name }}

This file is loaded by Claude Code when it begins work on the repository.
It is a Claude-specific superset of [AGENTS.md](AGENTS.md): everything in
AGENTS.md applies, plus the Claude-specific guidance below.

## Tone and style

- Match responses to the task. A simple question gets a direct answer,
  not headers and sections.
- Default to writing no comments. Add one when the WHY is non-obvious.
- Avoid backwards-compatibility hacks or speculative abstractions.

## Tool preferences

- Use `Edit` for targeted edits, `Write` only for new files or full
  rewrites.
- Use `TodoWrite` to track multi-step work.
- Run quality gates locally (lint, typecheck, tests) before declaring
  a task complete.

## What to confirm before acting

- Destructive operations (delete files, force-push, drop tables): always
  confirm before proceeding.
- Operations visible to others (push, open PR, send Slack message): always
  confirm.
- Uploading content to third-party tools (gist, pastebin, diagram
  renderers): consider whether the content is sensitive before sending.

## Definition of done

A task is done when:

1. The change accomplishes what was requested.
2. Tests pass.
3. Lint and typecheck pass.
4. Pre-commit hooks pass without `--no-verify`.

